  "abstract": "The credential records which public source-spine links and identities were included in a specific public-safe payload. Its SHA-256 fingerprint and OpenTimestamps proof make later changes detectable and can establish that the exact payload existed before a confirmed Bitcoin timestamp.",
  "usageInfo": "This is a first-party provenance credential, not an independent certification, accreditation, endorsement, ranking, insurance decision, government credential, or platform approval. It contains no customer records, private claim files, passwords, API keys, signing secrets, private project addresses, or live crew availability. A timestamp proves the existence and integrity of the payload, not the truth of every underlying statement."
